claude-devtools CLI

Usage: cdt [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  projects     Project operations
  sessions     Session listing and filtering
  session      Compact turn overview of a session (default) or raw chunks (--raw)
  turn         Single turn's complete steps (thinking, tool calls, text, etc.)
  tool-output  Full untruncated output of a tool call
  export       Export session as Markdown or JSON
  search       Full-text search across sessions
  stats        Aggregated usage statistics
  serve        Start HTTP API server
  mcp          MCP server mode
  setup        One-click setup (MCP registration + Skills installation)
  completions  Generate shell completion scripts
  self-update  Self-update to the latest version
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --format <FORMAT>    Output format [default: table] [possible values: json, jsonl, table]
      --project <PROJECT>  Scope to a project (name or encoded ID; use --project=<id> for encoded IDs)
      --json[=<JSON>]      Select JSON fields (comma-separated), implies --format json. Without value: list available fields. Usage: --json=field1,field2
      --no-truncate        Do not truncate fields in table mode
  -v, --verbose...         Increase diagnostic verbosity (-v warn, -vv info, -vvv debug). All output is silent by default; `RUST_LOG` overrides this entirely
  -h, --help               Print help
  -V, --version            Print version
